1:1 COMMENT "# os_spawn.z -- fork/exec child processes and read back exit codes."
1:68 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# `os.spawn` runs `argv[0]` (PATH-resolved via execvp) as a child with"
3:71 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# stdin from /dev/null and stdout/stderr redirected to the given paths;"
4:72 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# it returns the child's exit status. Spawning `true` and `false` is a"
5:71 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# deterministic 0 / 1 with no captured output to depend on. Letting main"
6:73 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# return normally (no os.exit) runs the argv destructors, so the leak"
7:70 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# gate stays clean."
8:20 EOL "\n"
9:1 EOL "\n"
